narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Absolutely - it is a great combination of philisophical discussion and close musical analysis. Hepokoski is even better in seminar than he is in lecture (which is saying something). Don't miss a chance to take a seminar with him.

If you looooooove Beethoven, German transcendental philosophy, and close structural analysis, you'll loooooooooove Beethovenian monuments. Be ready, though, to provisionally accept that listening to these pieces is the most important thing you've ever done in your life.
